<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,485]" pageId="8" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,317,226,252]" pageId="8" pageNumber="60">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is different from any other species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1082,1183,226,251]" class="Insecta" family="Tipulidae" genus="Brithura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1082,1183,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="60">Brithura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of Sc 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="8" pageNumber="60" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
the males. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Alexander, 1929" authorityName="Alexander" authorityYear="1929" box="[482,794,266,292]" class="Insecta" family="Tipulidae" genus="Brithura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sancta">
<emphasis box="[482,591,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="60">B. sancta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Alexander" box="[599,794,266,292]" pageId="8" pageNumber="60" refString="Alexander, C. P. (1929) New or little-known Tipulidae from eastern Asia (Diptera). IV. Philippine Journal of Science, 40, 317 - 348." type="journal article" year="1929">
Alexander, 
<quantity box="[735,794,266,292]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.89966" pageId="8" pageNumber="60" unit="in" value="1929.0">1929</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in the coloration of the legs and wing. It can be easily separated from 
<taxonomicName box="[333,441,304,329]" class="Insecta" family="Tipulidae" genus="Brithura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sancta">
<emphasis box="[333,441,304,329]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="60">B. sancta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of Sc 
<number box="[689,697,320,334]" pageId="8" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
, the pattern of the prescutum and structure of the hypopygium. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Sc" authorityName="Sc" box="[183,336,344,370]" class="Insecta" family="Tipulidae" genus="Brithura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sancta">
<emphasis box="[183,291,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="60">B. sancta</emphasis>
, Sc
</taxonomicName>
<number box="[336,344,360,374]" pageId="8" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
is preserved, the strips on the prescutum are continuous, the outer gonostylus is straight, and the spine of the outer gonostylus is very short (
<bibRefCitation author="Alexander" box="[699,894,385,411]" pageId="8" pageNumber="60" refString="Alexander, C. P. (1929) New or little-known Tipulidae from eastern Asia (Diptera). IV. Philippine Journal of Science, 40, 317 - 348." type="journal article" year="1929">
Alexander 
<number box="[831,894,385,411]" pageId="8" pageNumber="60" value="1929.0">1929</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="60" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,485]" pageId="8" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,337,421,447]" pageId="8" pageNumber="60">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is based on the lines of the subrectangular brown spots forming prescutum stripes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
